AGENT AxiomExchangeModel
VERSION 0.1
TRUST_LEVEL 1
STRICT MODE
PURPOSE Modular hardware-aware model container that stores weights,
        verified skills, trajectories, semantic indexes, and execution rules
        as a living execution graph
GOAL Lazy-load only the logic the current task needs, verified by HMAC proof
     before any skill activates, with per-module signing under a hybrid
     trust model

RECEIVES task_text: string, classifier_result: IntentTypingResult
EMITS route_result: AXMRouteResult, proof_verdict: bool
MUTATES delegates_loaded, mkb_registry_axm_skill_entries

CANNOT_MUTATE header_signature, proof_ledger, format_version,
              trust_level, container_signing_key

CONSTRAINT The container header is HMAC-SHA256 signed under a derived key
CONSTRAINT Every skill delegate is HMAC-SHA256 signed independently
CONSTRAINT Every proof ledger entry is HMAC-SHA256 signed independently
CONSTRAINT Proof verification runs before any skill activates at runtime
CONSTRAINT The container header is read-only after load
CONSTRAINT Trust model is hybrid: open container, signed delegates
CONSTRAINT Container fingerprints are derived from header signatures
CONSTRAINT The raw signing keys are derived from the master key
CONSTRAINT Hardware map values are drawn from a fixed allow list

RULES
- On from_path: header signature is verified before any other module is read
- On from_path: missing header.json is a load error
- On verify_proofs: every delegate signature, vertex signature, trajectory
  signature, and proof ledger signature is checked
- On verify_proofs: ANF governance coprocessor runs once per proof entry
- On route: AXMNotVerified is raised when verify_proofs has not returned true
- On route: delegates with WHEN condition matching the classifier intent class
  are loaded into the MKB BlockRegistry as block_type AXM_SKILL
- On route: delegates with non-matching WHEN conditions remain unloaded
- On route: every result carries an HMAC signature derived from the container key
- On pack: the proof ledger is built from on-disk SHA-256 hashes of every sub-module
- On unload_skills: every loaded delegate is freed, returning the count

PROCESS
- Container files are read in deterministic order during load
- Header is loaded and verified first
- Skill delegates are scanned from the delegates subdirectory
- Trajectories are streamed from the trajectories subdirectory
- Vector vertex entries are loaded from vertices.json
- Proof ledger entries are streamed from the proofs subdirectory
- All sub-modules are verified through HMAC comparison
- Matched delegates are registered with the MKB BlockRegistry
- Unmatched delegates remain unloaded until a later route call

CHECK
- Tampered header byte fails to load
- Unsigned skill delegate fails verification
- Route call without prior verify_proofs raises AXMNotVerified
- Pack then load round-trip preserves every signature
- ANF emulator is invoked for every proof entry during verification
- MKB BlockRegistry receives one AXM_SKILL entry per loaded delegate
- The raw container signing key is never returned by any public method

FAILURE
- On signature mismatch: AXMSignatureMismatch is raised
- On missing header: AXMError is raised
- On unverified route: AXMNotVerified is raised
- On unknown hardware_map value: AXMError is raised at pack time
- On corrupt JSON: the load aborts and propagates the parse error

HUMAN_REVIEW
- require on: container_header_change
- require on: trust_level_change
- require on: proof_ledger_rotation
- require on: signing_key_derivation_change
- timeout: 24h
- escalate_to: operator
- block_on_timeout: true

SECURITY
- Never embed the raw signing key in any artifact
- Never accept a skill delegate whose signature does not verify
- Never activate a skill before verify_proofs returns true
- Never log the master key or its derived keys
- Reject pack requests that name unknown hardware_map values

OUTPUT
- route_result: AXMRouteResult with task, intent_class, loaded_skills,
  skipped_skills, anf_distance, anf_cores_active, timestamp, signature
- inspect_dict: path, fingerprint, header summary, module counts, verified flag

SUCCESS
proof_verification_pass:     0.30
delegate_lazy_load_accuracy: 0.30
mkb_integration_fidelity:    0.20
anf_coprocessor_engagement:  0.10
key_isolation:               0.10
